From 46d104e6e2e94a1385df4c333c49dba9b1af0ab5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Peter Chiu <chui-hao.chiu@mediatek.com>
Date: Wed, 26 Mar 2025 15:11:44 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] mtk: mt76: mt7996: check MT76_SCANNING instead of
 dev->scan.chan

The dev->scan.chan is per-card variable and MT76_SCANNING is per-radio
variable. Without this patch, it would bypass dpd calibration if add
chanctx when the other band is scanning.

Signed-off-by: Peter Chiu <chui-hao.chiu@mediatek.com>
---
 mt7996/mcu.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/mt7996/mcu.c b/mt7996/mcu.c
index f7aeb8bf..8ece10bd 100644
--- a/mt7996/mcu.c
+++ b/mt7996/mcu.c
@@ -5561,7 +5561,7 @@ int mt7996_mcu_set_chan_info(struct mt7996_phy *phy, u16 tag, bool sta)
 		req.switch_reason = CH_SWITCH_NORMAL;
 	else if (phy->mt76->offchannel ||
 		 phy->mt76->hw->conf.flags & IEEE80211_CONF_IDLE ||
-		 dev->mt76.scan.chan)
+		 test_bit(MT76_SCANNING, &phy->mt76->state))
 		req.switch_reason = CH_SWITCH_SCAN_BYPASS_DPD;
 	else if (!cfg80211_reg_can_beacon(phy->mt76->hw->wiphy, chandef, iftype))
 		req.switch_reason = CH_SWITCH_DFS;
-- 
